body_html:
IIRC, it was lacking an _apply_dense() implementation, there were typos that caused failures when used, etc.

The commit is obviously in the history for somebody to re-use and fix, if they wanted, but they'd need to write more tests and probably refactor it to make it something that the team could accept to TensorFlow.

body:
IIRC, it was lacking an _apply_dense() implementation, there were typos that caused failures when used, etc.

The commit is obviously in the history for somebody to re-use and fix, if they wanted, but they'd need to write more tests and probably refactor it to make it something that the team could accept to TensorFlow.
